\c 11
\s1 Facing the uncertainties in life
\q1
\v 1 Sell your harvest to a foreign land,
\q2 because after some time, you will receive the profit.
\q1
\v 2 Divide your earnings to various businesses/efforts,
\q2 because you don’t know what disaster will happen.
\b
\q1
\v 3 When seeing that the cloud is already dark and contain much water, we don’t need to be amazed when rain falls.
\q2 Whatever direction a tree falls, then that tree will continue to stay there.
\q1
\v 4 Don’t be too influenced by your situation,
\q2 because if you always wait until the wind and weather becomes perfect,
\q2 you will never sow seeds and will never harvest the result.
\b
\q1
\v 5 As you can’t guess the direction the wind will blow,
\q2 or understand how the body of a baby is formed in the womb of his mother,
\q1 likewise you cannot understand the various work of God our Creator.
\b
\q1
\v 6 Sow your seeds in the morning, and do various other businesses/efforts until it is time to sleep at night.
\q1 Because you don’t know which business will be successful, or hopefully all of them will be successful
\s1 Remember your Creator in your youth
\q1
\v 7 How happy it is to see the sunlight in the morning.
\q2 How happy it feels to be alive.
